Shanghai - Yangpu Bridge
Shanghai's Yangpu Bridge (杨浦大桥) at night. For the World EXPO 2010 search lights have been installed along the bridge's main span, illuminating the sky with a giant light show every 15 minutes. This is the beginning of the show - the best looking part with the searchlights forming a fan. Automatic white balance. <a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/cnmark/4665809387/lightbox/">View large on a black background</a>.

Shot from the promenade besides the Qichangzhan ferry pier (其昌栈轮渡站). <a href="http://loc.alize.us/#/flickr:4665809387" rel="nofollow">See where this picture was taken.</a> <a href="http://www.flickr.com/groups/geotagging/discuss/72157594165549916/">[?]</a>

One giant floating crane is moored in the Huangpu River - blocking a bit of the view, but adding to the photo...

